    "name": "COU1: Total knee arthroplasty tibial tray fatigue (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite element model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of tibial tray fatigue life and polyethylene contact stress to variations in component geometry and patient loading conditions for a TKA device used in primary total knee replacement. Model influence is MEDIUM (physical bench testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact device fatigue life and patient safety). Model Risk Level 3.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FEA to identify worst-case loading configurations for tibial tray fatigue across 7 load-alignment combinations for a Class II TKA device. Results compared against physical fatigue bench test data using relative fatigue life index (RFL > 1 acceptance criterion) and contact stress within 15% of strain gauge measurements.",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
